git init - initialise the repository
git status - check the status of the repository
git add <file/folder> - add files/folders to track
git commit -m "added the files" - "m" option to provide message for this permanent track
git log - log of all the activities 

Linking and pushing to cloud repository
git remote add origin git@github.com:aroharamesh/gitdemo.git
git push -u origin master

For windows users:
Download - Gitbash - "right click on any folder which will give you gitbash here"